The paper deals with the complexity of model-checking for monadic second order logic on classes of graphs of bounded and unbounded tree-width. This topic is closely related to graph algorithms and computational complexity, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as it covers the study of algorithms and data structures for graphs. cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as it covers the study of logic and its applications in computer science. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another likely category as it covers the study of the complexity of computational problems. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) are less likely but still possible categories as they cover topics related to graphs and formal languages.
